---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const pageTitle = "About Bonnie Bostrom | Artist Statement";
---

<BaseLayout title={pageTitle} description="Artist statement and biography of Bonnie Bostrom.">
  <Nav />
  
  <main>
    <!-- 1. Header with Background Image -->
    <header class="about-header">
      <div class="header-bg">
        <img src="/images/about/about-hero.webp" alt="Background" loading="eager" />
        <div class="header-overlay"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="header-content container">
        <h1 class="page-title">Artist's Statement</h1>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- 2. Section 1: Text + Portrait 1 (Left Column Only) -->
    <section class="section about-intro first-intro">
      <div class="container container-wide">
        <div class="intro-grid">
          <div class="intro-col-content">
             <div class="intro-text-block">
                <h1 class="big-h1">Many times I have been encouraged to choose one particular avenue of creativity and concentrate my efforts there.</h1>
             </div>
             <div class="intro-image spacer-top">
                <img src="/images/about/bonnie-portrait-1.webp" alt="Bonnie Bostrom Portrait 1" />
             </div>
          </div>
          <div class="intro-col-empty">
            <!-- Empty Right Column -->
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <!-- 3. Section 2: Portrait 2 + Text (Right Column Only) -->
    <section class="section about-intro second-intro">
      <div class="container container-wide">
         <div class="intro-grid">
            <div class="intro-col-empty">
              <!-- Empty Left Column -->
            </div>
            <div class="intro-col-content">
               <div class="intro-image">
                  <img src="/images/about/bonnie-portrait-2.webp" alt="Bonnie Bostrom Portrait 2" />
               </div>
               <div class="intro-text-block spacer-top right-aligned-desktop">
                  <h1 class="big-h1">The thinking behind that advice was that I needed to devote myself to one endeavor so that I might become successful.</h1>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 6. "That didn't work for me" Section -->
    <section class="section statement-break">
      <div class="break-bg">
         <img src="/images/about/green-wash-bg.webp" alt="Green Wash Background" />
         <div class="green-overlay"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="break-content container">
        <h1 class="all-caps-centered">
          THAT<br/>
          DIDN'T<br/>
          WORK<br/>
          FOR ME.
        </h1>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 7-9. Writer Section -->
    <section class="section writer-section">
      <div class="container container-narrow">
        <p class="lead-text left-align">I am not torn between writing, composing, and painting. I find that I need several outlets.</p>
        
        <h2 class="subhead">I have always been a writer.</h2>
        
        <div class="text-content">
          <p>As soon as I learned cursive, I found I could write down my ideas quickly (printing is laborious) and loved writing poems. I also wrote little stories and created my own fairy tales. I have continued doing that my whole life.</p>
          <p>Some of the poems I wrote were like songs so when I was thirty I started to play the guitar and set my poems to music.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 10. BorderNoMargin Image -->
    <div class="full-width-image">
       <img src="/images/about/piano-strip.webp" alt="Bonnie at Piano" />
    </div>

    <!-- 11-12. Music Section -->
    <section class="section music-section">
       <div class="container container-narrow">
         <h2 class="subhead">I have written a lot of songs and love performing them.</h2>
         
         <div class="text-content">
            <p>The guitar was so much fun, I decided to try my hand at the piano and love it. If I get bored with writing, I play the piano or write a song.</p>
            <p>A friend, the musician 3 HAND STEPHEN, has recorded his arrangement of one of my songs, Atomic Clock, and I am writing more lyrics for him.</p>
            <p>Ten years ago, my sister, Jeanne Collins, suggested I try painting.</p>
         </div>
       </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 13. "Terrible Idea" Section (Reuse Design of Section 6) -->
    <section class="section statement-break">
      <div class="break-bg">
         <img src="/images/about/green-wash-bg.webp" alt="Green Wash Background" />
         <div class="green-overlay"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="break-content container">
        <h1 class="mid-caps-centered">
          I thought it was a terrible idea since I had tried oil painting at one time and it was a disaster. I had created a canvas of oil mud.
        </h1>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <!-- 14. Painting Section -->
    <section class="section painting-text-section">
      <div class="container container-narrow">
        <div class="text-content">
           <p>I could not stand waiting around for it to dry before I could continue.</p>
           <p>She suggested acrylics and took me to her studio to try it out. I loved it. I've been mad for painting since then and have finished literally hundreds of paintings.</p>
           <p>Thank goodness people like and buy them or I would run out of space!</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 15. Final 2 Column Section -->
    <section class="section closing-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="closing-grid">
           <!-- Column 1 -->
           <div class="closing-col-left">
              <img src="/images/about/bonnie-portrait-3.webp" alt="Bonnie Portrait 3" />
           </div>
           
           <!-- Column 2 -->
           <div class="closing-col-right">
              <h2>So I will continue with all my various pursuits because they make me happy.</h2>
              <p>Creating something that has never existed before is a great thrill to me, whether it is a book, a song, or a painting.</p>
              <p>I like to share what I have made in the hope that you will enjoy seeing the results of my creative process and that it will inspire you to create as well.</p>
              <p>And of course I would love to have you purchase a book or a painting!</p>
              
              <div class="signature-block">
                 <img src="/images/about/signature.webp" alt="Bonnie Bostrom Signature" />
              </div>
           </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* 1. Header */
  .about-header {
    height: 400px;
    position: relative;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  
  .header-bg {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
  }
  
  .header-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4); /* Dark overlay for text readability */
  }
  
  .header-content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
    text-align: center;
  }
  
  .page-title {
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 4.5rem); 
    color: #fff;
    text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
    margin: 0;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  /* Shared Container Widths */
  .container-wide {
    max-width: 1200px; /* Restored to wider to allow empty cols to work well */
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .container-narrow {
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  /* 2-3 Intro Sections */
  .about-intro {
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }
  
  .first-intro {
     padding-top: 4rem;
  }
  
  .intro-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
  }
  
  .intro-col-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  
  .spacer-top {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .big-h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: #662b5c;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0;
  }
  
  .right-aligned-desktop {
    text-align: right;
  }
  
  .intro-image img {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  
  /* 6 & 13 Break Sections (Green Wash) */
  .statement-break {
    position: relative;
    padding: 10rem 1rem; /* Increased padding for height/"breath" */
    text-align: center;
    color: #fff;
    overflow: hidden;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  
  .break-bg {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    z-index: -1;
  }
  
  .break-bg img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
  }
  
  .green-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    background-color: rgba(0, 100, 0, 0.4); /* Transparent green layer */
  }
  
  .break-content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
  }
  
  .all-caps-centered {
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.1;
    text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
  }
  
  .mid-caps-centered {
     font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.5rem);
     font-weight: 600;
     line-height: 1.4;
     max-width: 900px;
     margin: 0 auto;
     text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
  }

  /* Text Sections */
  .lead-text {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    color: #333;
  }
  
  .left-align {
    text-align: left;
  }
  
  .subhead {
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: #662b5c;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }
  
  .text-content p {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: #444;
  }
  
  /* 10 Full Width Image */
  .full-width-image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    /* Removed box-shadow */
  }

  /* 15 Closing Section */
  .closing-section {
    padding-bottom: 6rem;
  }
  
  .closing-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: start;
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  
  .closing-col-left img {
    width: 100%;
    /* Removed box-shadow */
  }
  
  .closing-col-right h2 {
    color: #662b5c;
    font-size: 2rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .closing-col-right p {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: #444;
  }
  
  .signature-block {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    width: 60%; 
  }
  
  .signature-block img {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
    /* Removed box-shadow */
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .intro-grid, 
    .closing-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }
    
    /* Hide empty columns on mobile if they take up space, 
       but with 1fr they just stack. We want content to take full width. */
    .intro-col-empty {
      display: none;
    }

    /* User Request: "Left align 'The thinking behind...' on mobile" */
    .right-aligned-desktop {
      text-align: left;
    }
    
    .about-header {
      height: 300px;
    }
    
    .page-title {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
